          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Original concern:<\/strong> Overall appropriations and funding for the judicial branch, including whether more judicial bandwidth is needed to handle high-volume executive-branch litigation and emergency dockets.<\/li><li><strong>Decision:<\/strong> Admitted as a new candidate issue; static HOR ID retained.<\/li><li><strong>Integrated into:<\/strong> JUD-010 in <a href=\"../../areas/JUD/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-04<\/a>.<\/li><li><strong>Rationale:<\/strong> Judicial capacity and appropriations are distinct from JUD-001 enforcement and JUD-009 recusal. Underfunding, insufficient judgeships, inadequate staffing, court-security constraints, and outdated court technology can make timely judicial review unavailable in practice even where legal remedies exist.<\/li><li><strong>Follow-up:<\/strong> Source-develop Judicial Conference budget requests, AO reports, caseload and weighted-filing data, JUDGES Act history, court-security funding, defender and magistrate capacity, emergency docket practices, court technology, and bipartisan prior proposals before drafting.<\/li><\/ul>",
          "search_text": "HOR-017 HOR-017 2026-06-25 Admitted or promoted JUD-010 in A-04. HOR-017 2026-06-25 Admitted or promoted JUD-010 in A-04."
