          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Original concern:<\/strong> Puerto Rico political-status resolution, statehood or nonterritorial self-determination, and democratic representation.<\/li><li><strong>Decision:<\/strong> Retired without admission as outside scope; static HOR ID and closed GitHub issue <a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/issues/19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">#19<\/a> retained as the permanent intake record; inactive card removed from the GitHub Project.<\/li><li><strong>Integrated into:<\/strong> Not integrated into an issue. Scope boundaries recorded in <a href=\"../../areas/ELEC/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-02<\/a>, <a href=\"../../areas/FED/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-20<\/a>, and <a href=\"../../areas/RIGHTS/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-24<\/a>.<\/li><li><strong>Rationale:<\/strong> Selecting among statehood, independence, free association, territorial status, or another final political arrangement is a substantive political choice for Puerto Rico&#x27;s electorate and Congress. The continuing absence of a final resolution is a political failure unless a candidate identifies a distinct defect in a legally operative process; ARRP should not substitute its preferred status or create a mechanism designed to force one substantive result.<\/li><li><strong>Follow-up:<\/strong> Do not reopen final-status selection as an ARRP objective. Create a new, narrow horizon candidate only if evidence identifies a separable election, adjudication, due-process, rights-administration, benefit-access, disaster-governance, federalism, or territorial-administration defect with a status-neutral remedy.<\/li><\/ul>",
