          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Original concern:<\/strong> Foreign election interference and campaign counterintelligence safeguards arising from the Mueller Report foreign-interference record and related Durham/FISA process source-development questions.<\/li><li><strong>Decision:<\/strong> Retained as a deferred horizon candidate; static HOR ID retained.<\/li><li><strong>Integrated into:<\/strong> Active GitHub horizon issue <a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/issues/234\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">#234<\/a>; possible future home in <a href=\"../../areas/ELEC/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-02<\/a>; source-development cross-references to <a href=\"../../areas/DOJ/issues/DOJ-003.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DOJ-003<\/a>, <a href=\"../../areas/DOJ/issues/DOJ-007.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DOJ-007<\/a>, <a href=\"../../areas/CLASS/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-07<\/a>, <a href=\"../../areas/CONG/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-15<\/a>, and <a href=\"../../areas/FACT/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">A-18<\/a>.<\/li><li><strong>Rationale:<\/strong> Existing ARRP election proposals address domestic executive interference, certification, transition, campaign finance, and electoral competition, but they do not cleanly own foreign cyber operations, foreign digital influence, hacked-material handling, campaign-contact safeguards, campaign-related counterintelligence predicates, FISA accuracy duties, or classified oversight. The issue is potentially important but should not be developed without national-security, election-security, counterintelligence, FISA, cyber, and First Amendment expertise.<\/li><li><strong>Follow-up:<\/strong> If experts join the project, source-develop the <a href=\"../../research/mueller-report-arrp-crosswalk.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mueller Report crosswalk<\/a>, <a href=\"../../research/durham-report-arrp-crosswalk.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Durham Report crosswalk<\/a>, Senate Intelligence Committee Russian active-measures reports, the 2017 Intelligence Community Assessment, IRA and GRU indictments, DOJ Inspector General Crossfire Hurricane/FISA materials, FISC orders, FISA reform history, CISA election-security guidance, campaign-contact rules, hacked-material handling rules, and foreign digital influence safeguards; then decide whether to admit a dedicated A-02 issue or split election-security and FISA/counterintelligence remedies.<\/li><\/ul>",
          "search_text": "HOR-023 HOR-023 2026-07-02 Deferred or monitoring Active GitHub horizon issue #234; possible future home in A-02; source-development cross-references to DOJ-003, DOJ-007, A-07, A-15, and A-18. HOR-023 2026-07-02 Deferred or monitoring Active GitHub horizon issue #234; possible future home in A-02; source-development cross-references to DOJ-003, DOJ-007, A-07, A-15, and A-18."
