          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Change audited:<\/strong> Project-wide consistency, lifecycle, Console, source-development, intake, publication, and automation closeout<\/li><li><strong>Scope:<\/strong> Project Console queue and disclosure conventions; GitHub <code>Development level<\/code> and workflow <code>Status<\/code>; delegated-foundation authority; Change Audit metadata; reader navigation and terminology; area and issue ownership; legislative drafting form; external-source versus internal-work provenance; Horizon and area source-development descriptions; public-intake security; GitHub and publication readback; deterministic Integrity coverage; and full validation.<\/li><li><strong>Score/rebaseline effect:<\/strong> No Proposal Quality Score, scoring rubric, threshold, score band, Review Ready determination, rebaseline, or <strong>Runs<\/strong> count changed. Lifecycle and workflow fields were synchronized only to their already established canonical meanings.<\/li><li><strong>Findings and corrections:<\/strong> Standardized Console queues around accountable owners, meaningful counts, compact indexes, expandable records, persistent layouts, and separate current-problem versus history views. Separated substantive maturity into six <code>Development level<\/code> stages from the workflow-only <code>Status<\/code>; migrated and read back all 99 then-active records and replaced <code>Defined proposal<\/code> with <code>In development<\/code>. Clarified the four-part foundation, Elim and interactive-agent sufficiency authority, and the human-reserved boundary; APPT-001, JUD-012, OVS-009, REG-002, and RIGHTS-005 were initially identified for that check and were later reconciled in the Elim run recorded in <code>ELIM_RUN_LOG.md<\/code>. Paired <code>change_audit_needed<\/code> with a reason on 22 revised records without changing scores or Runs. Linked resolvable identifiers, translated reader-facing internal shorthand, restored concise area directories, created the PRESS-003 issue stub and source-development owner, and routed HER-001 research to its issue-specific record. Added standard enacting clauses and normalized metadata, hierarchy, and drafting-note form across ten federal drafts without claiming provision-by-provision legal validation. Removed an ARRP-authored research item from the external bibliography, retained its internal project citation, added three external PRESS-003 sources, and preserved the requirement for separate generated external-source and ARRP-material lists in final print assembly. Replaced empty relevance text in HOR-040, HOR-041, HOR-042, and HOR-044 with candidate-specific comparison questions; those questions remained source-specific analysis work, and any <code>Reviewed: Yes<\/code> entry required reconciliation with unfinished analysis. Replaced 148 generic descriptions in 24 area research records with qualified source- and title-specific propositions while leaving qualitative public placement for ordinary development. Removed public GitHub issue-form and blank-issue bypasses, obsolete email exposure, and generated-route drift; preserved ongoing dependency, deployment, and abuse monitoring. Repaired stale GitHub links on issues 8, 14, and 203 and synchronized PRESS-003&#x27;s Project canonical page. Expanded Integrity checks for YAML, generated routes, Change Audit pairing, foundation decisions, legislative metadata and enacting clauses, H1 structure, source URL schemes, generic source-development text, cross-issue links, and authenticated GitHub synchronization; external URL availability remained the Source Checker Bot&#x27;s report-only responsibility and no complete baseline yet existed. Final validation covered Python and Node tests, language syntax, ShellCheck, structured data, diff hygiene, strict MkDocs build, authenticated GitHub synchronization, and live Vercel security headers; the authenticated consistency audit then reported zero deterministic errors and warnings, without claiming universal external-source availability, resolving human foundation decisions, or assigning new proposal scores.<\/li><\/ul>",
