          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Change audited:<\/strong> GitHub-native issue monitoring and evidence-route visibility<\/li><li><strong>Scope:<\/strong> Project-wide monitoring workflow: GitHub Project Status options, native source-review sub-issue convention, issue-specific <code>ISSUE-ID-MON<\/code> naming, multi-issue source routing, source-intake dashboard linkage, agent operating rules, active monitoring inventory, GitHub issue registry, reader-facing monitoring/evidence links, and qualitative evidence-record linkage.<\/li><li><strong>Score/rebaseline effect:<\/strong> No Proposal Quality Score, rubric version, rebaseline, Review Ready determination, or <strong>Runs<\/strong> count changed. <code>Monitoring<\/code> is a workflow status exclusively for monitoring sub-issues; it does not replace a parent proposal&#x27;s lifecycle status. The reader-navigation links and DOM-005 evidence record do not alter institutional diagnosis, remedy, legislation, or audited score.<\/li><li><strong>Findings and corrections:<\/strong> Established one native <code>ISSUE-ID-MON<\/code> source-review sub-issue for each coherent live proposal monitoring stream, with <code>kind: source review<\/code>, <code>needs: monitoring<\/code>, a native parent relationship, Project <code>Monitoring<\/code> status, and a defined external predicate. Twenty-four proposal-level monitoring records now consolidate 175 active proposal-routed external matters; four Horizon-only matters remain on their existing active Horizon records rather than receiving duplicate children. Each matter retains one primary analytic home and may have affected-issue links, preventing case-history and source duplication. The GitHub Project&#x27;s existing Monitoring view is the operational review surface; the intake console remains read-only aggregation and now links each monitoring record to its GitHub home. Every developed parent page with an active monitor now ends <strong>Manifestation of the Failure<\/strong> with a concise <strong>Supporting Record and Updates<\/strong> subsection. It links to the active monitor as <strong>Watching for updates<\/strong> and, when justified, to a linked evidence record as <strong>Additional supporting record<\/strong>. Undeveloped records remain tracked through their GitHub parent and monitor without manufacturing placeholder pages. DOM-005 received the first record under this convention because the page is already supported by a substantial, source-identified official access chronology and the separate record materially improves organization and ongoing monitoring; other monitored pages retain only their watch link because their additional material is still primarily pending verification, cumulative, or insufficiently distinct for reader-facing annex treatment. A project-wide monitoring pass is non-scoring, refreshes posture and triggers, updates source/evidence placement, and closes resolved records; a material result still requires the ordinary targeted Change Audit and Internal Remedy-Fit review.<\/li><\/ul>",
