          "details_html": "<ul><li><strong>Change audited:<\/strong> GitHub Project sync failure disclosure rule<\/li><li><strong>Scope:<\/strong> Targeted Change Audit of audit-completion workflow in <code>AGENT_OPERATING_RULES.md<\/code> and <code>GITHUB_WORKFLOW.md<\/code> after a Project-field sync blocker was discovered during ELEC-012 follow-up.<\/li><li><strong>Score/rebaseline effect:<\/strong> No proposal-quality score change, no rubric-version change, and no proposal rebaseline required. This is a workflow and reporting rule that treats Project fields as completion-critical tracking metadata; it does not alter scoring weights, score bands, or existing issue substance.<\/li><li><strong>Findings and corrections:<\/strong> Added a rule that when audit work changes GitHub Project fields, the Project row must be updated before the task is reported complete. If the agent cannot update the Project row because of authentication, permissions, API, tooling, sandbox, or connector limits, the agent must notify the user clearly as soon as the failure is known, identify the affected issue and fields, preserve the repo work, and treat the task as blocked or partially complete until Project access is fixed or the user accepts a repo-only interim state. Issue-body snapshots are allowed only as temporary visibility fallbacks, not replacements for Project fields.<\/li><\/ul>",
